    {
      "id": "0CLZiUsq2KqlFNAxdAs7U",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 348.5448284828037,
      "y": 114.28627800206962,
      "width": 1395.8859945149725,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a6",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1398428848,
      "version": 138,
      "versionNonce": 1018657968,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777534706016,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "  So the sequence is:\n  1. Headlamp frontend loads, reads IndexedDB, calls parseKubeConfig → gets cluster name → stores in Redux → navigates to /c/<alias>\n  2. Headlamp frontend immediately fires some initial requests to that cluster\n  3. Those requests go through BFF → BFF adds KUBECONFIG header → Headlamp backend handles them fine\n  4. But Headlamp's frontend shows the error banner because the initial check (before the backend cache is populated) failed",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "  So the sequence is:\n  1. Headlamp frontend loads, reads IndexedDB, calls parseKubeConfig → gets cluster name → stores in Redux → navigates to /c/<alias>\n  2. Headlamp frontend immediately fires some initial requests to that cluster\n  3. Those requests go through BFF → BFF adds KUBECONFIG header → Headlamp backend handles them fine\n  4. But Headlamp's frontend shows the error banner because the initial check (before the backend cache is populated) failed",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "0FJUDGrx6-lGBXAfjQeTd",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 350.07137454765757,
      "y": -45.75556623595088,
      "width": 1577.85291049069,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a7",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2055194704,
      "version": 110,
      "versionNonce": 589225040,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777534734302,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "  The flow:\n  1. Frontend calls a new POST /api/headlamp-kubeconfig BFF endpoint with { kubeconfig: base64string } to store it in the session\n  2. BFF proxy reads headlamp_kubeconfig from session and adds it as KUBECONFIG header on all /api/headlamp/* requests\n  3. Headlamp backend receives the KUBECONFIG header, loads the cluster context per-request — fully stateless, no IndexedDB needed\n  4. The iframe-bridge plugin is no longer needed for cluster registration at all",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "  The flow:\n  1. Frontend calls a new POST /api/headlamp-kubeconfig BFF endpoint with { kubeconfig: base64string } to store it in the session\n  2. BFF proxy reads headlamp_kubeconfig from session and adds it as KUBECONFIG header on all /api/headlamp/* requests\n  3. Headlamp backend receives the KUBECONFIG header, loads the cluster context per-request — fully stateless, no IndexedDB needed\n  4. The iframe-bridge plugin is no longer needed for cluster registration at all",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
